                     Minginater: One that makes Fretwork;
it is a ruſtick word uſed in ſome prat of Yorkſhire,
corrupted perchance from engine.

To Pote the clothes off; to kick all off;
to puſh or put out, from the French Pouſſer
or Poſer, pulſare, or ponere, to put.

                     Thone, thong; meâ ſententiâ q. thawn;
Damp, moiſt. Skinner à Teut. Tuncken,
